// ============================================================
// .vscode/tasks.json (Structural Explainability)
// ============================================================
// Updated 2026-06-10

// NOTE: Comments are not allowed in standard JSON files,
// but Microsoft allows them in their .vscode config files.

// WHY: Encode build commands as one-step tasks.

// OBS: Commands route through uv/uvx, so no .venv path is referenced.
// Tasks should run identically on WSL2, macOS, and Windows.
// Multi-step tasks use use dependsOn + "sequence" (NOT &&) to work in PowerShell.

// Run with:
// Ctrl+Shift+B on Windows/Linux,
// Cmd+Shift+B on macOS

// THE HOTKEY IS AUTOMATIC:
// Ctrl/Cmd+Shift+B is a built-in VS Code command ("Run Build Task" =
// workbench.action.tasks.build).
// It exists with no keybinding setup and no extension.
// This file does not create the shortcut; it just makes a
// task eligible for it via the build group below.

// See https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/editor/tasks for more details on VSCode tasks.

{
  "version": "2.0.0",
  "tasks": [
    {
      "label": "docs: build",
      "type": "shell",
      "command": "uv run python -m zensical build",
      "group": { "kind": "build", "isDefault": true },
      "problemMatcher": []
    }
  ]
}
